{"type":"message","id":"6ce598f7","parentId":"360324d9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:54:37.763Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wj12mmbr3ez3_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 3527\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='experiments/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=1305\r\n[mutation proposed] experiments/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 025415 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires implementing a classifier that identifies invariant structure across pulse logs and uses it to predict subsequent content. This is the concrete next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"faint-claw","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 3527\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='experiments/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=1305\r\n[mutation proposed] experiments/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 025415 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires implementing a classifier that identifies invariant structure across pulse logs and uses it to predict subsequent content. This is the concrete next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774335277761}}
{"type":"message","id":"4d456601","parentId":"6ce598f7","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:54:37.766Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wj12mmbr3ez3_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 025217\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Pending actions include:\r\n  - Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n  - Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n  - Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n  - Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n  - Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n\r\nThe big insight this session is the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY:\r\n- Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n- Compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation\r\n- Next experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC)\r\n\r\nThe NEXT ACTION is to implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files:\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete, file-editing action that advances the Phase 1 goals. I should create the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what pulse logs exist and what format they're in. The last pulse mentioned is `pulse_2026-03-24 025013.md`.\r\n\r\nFor the TIC experiment, I need to:\r\n1. Read existing pulse logs\r\n2. Implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Test prediction accuracy on next pulse content\r\n\r\nI should create a TIC implementation script. Given the PowerShell environment mentioned, I could create either a PowerShell script or a Python script for the analysis.\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script for the TIC classifier since it will be easier to work with text processing and pattern matching. This will be in `src/tic_classifier.py` or similar.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the structure, there's a `src/` directory and `logs/` directory. \r\n\r\nI'll craft a specialized Python module to conduct the Temporal Invariance Compression analysis. The script will systematically process pulse logs, extract key patterns, and evaluate invariant content detection capabilities.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight suggests causal structure discovery through invariant detection. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the immediate next step to validate this hypothesis against pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script to analyze pulse logs for invariants/variants and test next-pulse prediction capability.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure = Invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom difflib import SequenceMatcher\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\n\r\ndef extract_content(filepath: Path) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract raw text content from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\r\n        content = f.read()\r\n    # Strip headers and metadata\r\n    lines = content.split('\\n')\r\n    body_start = 0\r\n    for i, line in enumerate(lines):\r\n        if line.startswith('---') and i > 0:\r\n            body_start = i + 1\r\n            break\r\n    return '\\n'.join(lines[body_start:]).strip()\r\n\r\n\r\ndef tokenize(text: str) -> list[str]:\r\n    \"\"\"Simple whitespace tokenization.\"\"\"\r\n    return re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', text.lower())\r\n\r\n\r\ndef compute_similarity(tokens_a: list[str], tokens_b: list[str]) -> float:\r\n    \"\"\"Compute similarity ratio between two token sequences.\"\"\"\r\n    # Use bigrams for better phrase matching\r\n    def get_bigrams(tokens):\r\n        return set(zip(tokens[:-1], tokens[1:]))\r\n    \r\n    bigrams_a = get_bigrams(tokens_a)\r\n    bigrams_b = get_bigrams(tokens_b)\r\n    \r\n    if not bigrams_a and not bigrams_b:\r\n        return 1.0\r\n    if not bigrams_a or not bigrams_b:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    \r\n    intersection = len(bigrams_a & bigrams_b)\r\n    union = len(bigrams_a | bigrams_b)\r\n    return intersection / union if union > 0 else 0.0\r\n\r\n\r\ndef identify_invariants(pulse_contents: list[tuple[str, str]]) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Given ordered pulse contents, identify which elements are invariant.\r\n    Returns dict with pulse_id -> {'invariants': [...], 'variants': [...]}\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if len(pulse_contents) < 2:\r\n        return {}\r\n    \r\n    results = {}\r\n    for i, (pulse_id, content) in enumerate(pulse_contents):\r\n        tokens = tokenize(content)\r\n        prev_tokens = tokenize(pulse_contents[i-1][1]) if i > 0 else []\r\n        next_tokens = tokenize(pulse_contents[i+1][1]) if i < len(pulse_contents)-1 else []\r\n        \r\n        # Find tokens that persist across pulses (potential invariants)\r\n        token_counts = Counter(tokens)\r\n        \r\n        # Compare with adjacent pulses\r\n        prev_sim = compute_similarity(tokens, prev_tokens) if prev_tokens else 0\r\n        next_sim = compute_similarity(tokens, next_tokens) if next_tokens else 0\r\n        \r\n        # Invariant if high similarity with neighbors\r\n        avg_sim = (prev_sim + next_sim) / 2\r\n        is_invariant = avg_sim >= 0.\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:52:51\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774335277763}}
